news.title: Haryana RERA orders forensic audit of Mahira Group's five affordable housing projects
news.para: According to a DTCP order, the developer fabricated bank guarantees and forged signatures of bank officials on the documents submitted to the department for procuring the licences of its affordable housing projects.

news.title: Gurugram: Takeover of seven private colonies complete, two more likely today
news.para: While the developers of Sushant Lok-2 and 3, Malibu Towne, Vipul World, Rosewood City, Uppal Southend and Ardee City have handed them over to the corporation, the takeover of Greenwood City and Mayfield Garden is still pending.

news.title: SBI hikes minimum interest rate on home loans to 7.55%
news.para: The lender has hiked its External Benchmark-based Lending Rate (EBLR) to a minimum of 7.55 per cent effective today as compared to 7.05 per cent earlier, as per the bank's website.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh waives stamp duty if property transferred to 'family member'
news.para: Minister for stamps and registration Ravindra Jaiswal said that the earlier stamp duty was creating unnecessary tension within families as the high court of registration was now allowing them to settle property issues while the owner was alive.

news.title: IBBI amends rules for swifter redressal of grievances filed against insolvency professionals
news.para: ​IBBI has amended the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Board of India (Grievance and Complaint Handling Procedure) Regulations, 2017 and the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Board of India (Inspection and Investigation) Regulations, 2017, according to an official release on Wednesday.

news.title: UP RERA to use provisions of civil procedure code for implementation of its orders
news.para: In the 94th meeting of the authority, a more effective policy for implementation of orders passed by RERA on complaints of allottees was laid down.

news.title: NCLT dismisses Gateway Offshore's insolvency plea against Pune-based Runwal Realtors
news.para: The Mumbai bench of the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT), while rejecting the arguments made by Gateway Offshore in its petition, observed that in absence of any written document indicating the purpose of the transactions between the parties, it cannot be assumed to have been towards a loan.

news.title: Private equity and venture capital funds shift focus to realty and infra from tech
news.para: ​However, compared with USD 7.5 billion of infusion in April, the investments were down by 29 per cent, the report by industry lobby IVCA and consultancy firm EY said. From a deal volume perspective, there were 109 transactions in May as against 66 in the year-ago period and 117 in April 2022.

news.title: Real estate brokers Compass, Redfin to cut jobs as housing market cools
news.para: Compass said it will layoff 450 employees, about 10% of its current workforce, and Redfin will cut about 470 jobs, about 6% of its total workforce.

news.title: Punargeham rehabilitation scheme fails to impress in Ernakulam
news.para: ​Since the project’s launch in 2019, only around 240 families have shown interest even though more than 1,600 families between Chellanam and Munambam were identified.

news.title: GST applicable on voluntary payments made by members to housing societies: AAR
news.para: AAR said that the money received by the society was for the supply of services. GST has a concept called "supply of services," which is used to figure out if a transaction is taxable or not. The AAR cited parts of the Model Bye Laws that say the society can't accept a payment from a transferor or transferee that was made on their own.

news.title: Chandigarh administration may use helpline 112 for illegal constructions
news.para: Presently, people inform the field staff who sometimes reveal the identity of the informer, leading to trouble. A senior official said the issue was recently raised before UT adviser Dharam Pal.

news.title: IIT Delhi develops low cost braces to enhance earthquake resistance in buildings
news.para: According to officials, the braces, for which a patent has also been applied have several advantages, such as all-steel components, on-site fabrication and assembling process, post-earthquake inspection, and easy replacement.

news.title: Police attach Lucknow-based realtor's assets worth Rs 116 crore
news.para: The accused, Paresh Rastogi, has been booked under Gangsters Act. He is named in 82 cases in police stations of Hazratganj, Vibhuti Khand, Gosainganj and others in Lucknow as well as in other districts.

news.title: Over 1.5 lakh houses out of tax net, will send notices to clear dues: Ghaziabad civic body
news.para: After the GMC’s survey, which began last year, the authority will send notices to the house owners, asking them to clear their dues.
